<p>Or <a href="http://contactless.tfl.gov.uk">create an account</a>.</p>

<h2>Transfer your credit or ticket to a new card by phone</h2>

<p><a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/buying-tickets-and-oyster">Get a new Oyster card</a>&nbsp;and make at least one journey with it, then call <a href="tel:0343 222 1234">0343 222 1234</a>&nbsp;(<a href="/corporate/terms-and-conditions/tfl-call-charges">Charges may&nbsp;apply</a>).</p>

<p>We'll arrange to transfer your credit or ticket to your new card.</p>

<h2>After you get your new card</h2>

<p>Your new Oyster card will have the same Travelcard, Bus &amp; Tram Pass and/or pay as you go credit that was on it before.</p>

<p>If you get discounted travel, you'll need to have the discount added to your replacement card:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Take your discount photocard and your Oyster card to any <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/oyster-ticket-stops">Oyster Ticket Stop</a> or Tube station</li>
	<li>Ask staff to add your discount to your Oyster card. You need to give a password</li>
	<li>Add pay as you go credit to your Oyster card</li>
	<li>Create or sign in to your <a href="/fares/contactless-and-oyster-account">contactless and Oyster account</a> and add your Oyster card. Use the same password you gave to staff when they added your discount. If you don't, you can't get a refund or replacement&nbsp;</li>
</ol>

<p>Carry your photocard and Oyster card with you at all times and don't let anyone else use your cards.</p>

<p>We may refund you for any travel you've had to pay for while waiting for your ticket or credit to be transferred.</p>

<p>If you have an Annual Travelcard, we'll send you a new Gold Record Card.</p>
